{
  "stem": "2522.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was really not too many places to go.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was hard to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or that, that was for young people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, the aliyahs accelerated, of course, in-- after '39.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But most of the Jews who were elderly and had family and houses just couldn't visualize themselves going somewhere-- picking themselves up and going somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Jews who left were wealthy lawyers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Specifically, I remember two families, wealthy lawyers who had connections with, with, with people abroad.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a particular family, the Pecek family, who was a very rich family, bankers, whose children had been educated in England, they just took off and left.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, my father's business continued as before.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] As a safeguard, my father tried to arrange it so that some of his friends, if his business would be expropriated, it would be expropriated by, by people who had a personal relationship with him, which subsequently actually happened.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the, the decisive step was the proclamation of the Slovak State, independent state, in March of 1939.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And part of the pledge was that the Slovak State would adopt the Nuremberg laws.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In many respects, it was seen as, as a viable solution for many of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they said, well, we are just going to hunker down.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we'll live with the Nuremberg laws.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At least the Nazis will not come because the people we know, these are the people you've always done business with.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You can do business with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we're going to try to negotiate incrementally what kind of a deal we can make.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so the first restrictions came in 1939.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
